myopenmath.statement:
Sunny is making candles in the shape of a cylinder. She needs to determine how many cubic centimeters of wax she needs.


Suppose the radius of the candle is 3.0 cm and the height of the candle is 9.0 cm.  Round using significant figures.




 How much wax is needed for one candle?  \displaystyle\text{cm}^{{3}}

 How much wax is needed for 20 candles?  \displaystyle\text{cm}^{{3}}

 If wax is sold in cubic meters, how many complete candles can be made with 1 cubic meter of wax?  candles

Hint: 1 cubic m = 1,000,000 cubic cm
